<exercise checkit-seed="0002" checkit-slug="FO4" checkit-title="Exact First-Order IVPs">
  <statement>
    <p>
        Explain why one of the following ODEs is exact, and why the other is not.
    </p>
      <me>-4 \, t^{2} {y'} + 4 \, t y {y'} - 8 \, t y = 10 \, t^{2} y {y'} + 10 \, t y^{2} - 2 \, y^{2}</me><me>10 \, t^{2} y {y'} = -8 \, t y + 2 \, y^{2} + 3 \, t {y'}</me>
    <p>
      Then find an implicit solution for the exact ODE
      that satisfies the initial value
        <m>y(-1)=1</m>.
    </p>
  </statement>
  <answer>
    <p>The following ODE is exact.</p>
      <me>-4 \, t^{2} {y'} + 4 \, t y {y'} - 8 \, t y = 10 \, t^{2} y {y'} + 10 \, t y^{2} - 2 \, y^{2}</me>
    <p>
      Its implicit solution satisfying the initial value is:
    </p>
      <me>-5 \, t^{2} y^{2} - 4 \, t^{2} y + 2 \, t y^{2} = \left(-11\right)</me>
  </answer>
</exercise>
